properties.title: ESRI International User Conference
properties.description:
Esri International User Conference | July 11–15, 2011 | San Diego, CA
Where Technology Sparks Your Imagination
However you use GIS, the Esri International User Conference (Esri UC) offers ways to do it better. This one-of-a-kind event is your opportunity to explore the power of geospatial technology and join a thriving community of GIS professionals who are passionate about their work.

properties.title: Urban Areas Security Initiative Workshop
properties.description:
On March 21-22, 2011, the AHC states and urban areas from around the Mid-Atlantic and North East Regions will hold the 2nd Annual Regional Urban Areas Security Initiatives and Planning Workshop to focus on coordinated planning and projects between government and private sector owner/operators within several industry sectors.

 Coordination across the region between government and private sector owners and operators of businesses is a constant challenge. The issues are complex, the stakeholders are many, and the progress has been slow for a variety of reasons. Fundamental to most of these issues are the people; the plans and planning efforts; and the projects that are invested into to address specific requirements and needs. Based on their combined experience over the past 6 years, the states and urban areas of the All Hazards Consortium have adopted a new “integrated planning and coordinated investment ” approach designed to integrate the private sector owner/operators into the planning and project development efforts with some of the regional states/UASIs and the federal partners. The 2nd Annual Regional Urban Areas Security Initiatives & Planning Workshop will be the first workshop under the AHC’s new strategy.
